name: python-jsonrpc-server
raw_meta_yaml:
{% set name = "python-jsonrpc-server" %}
{% set version = "0.4.0" %}

package:
  name: {{ name|lower }}
  version: {{ version }}

source:
  url: https://pypi.io/packages/source/{{ name[0] }}/{{ name }}/{{ name }}-{{ version }}.tar.gz
  sha256: 62c543e541f101ec5b57dc654efc212d2c2e3ea47ff6f54b2e7dcb36ecf20595

build:
  noarch: python
  number: 0
  script: {{ PYTHON }} -m pip install . --no-deps --ignore-installed --no-cache-dir -vvv

requirements:
  host:
    - python
    - pip
  run:
    - python
    - future
    - ujson >=3.0.0

test:
  requires:
    - pip
  imports:
    - pyls_jsonrpc
    - pyls_jsonrpc.dispatchers
  commands:
    - python -m pip check

about:
  home: https://github.com/palantir/python-jsonrpc-server
  license: MIT
  license_file: LICENSE
  license_family: MIT
  summary: A Python 2.7 and 3.4+ server implementation of the JSON RPC 2.0 protocol.
  dev_url: https://github.com/palantir/python-jsonrpc-server

extra:
  recipe-maintainers:
    - ccordoba12
    - andfoy
smithy_version:
No azure token. Create a token and
